## Findings
- URL: https://github.com/z-lab/dflash
- Description: DFlash (Block Diffusion for Flash Speculative Decoding) is a technology designed to dramatically speed up LLM (Large Language Model) inference.
- Use Case: Accelerating text generation for various models like Qwen, Gemma, etc., by using a "drafting" mechanism.
- LLM/Performance context: It achieves significant speedups (up to 8.5x compared to standard autoregressive generation) while remaining "lossless" (the output is identical to the base model). It uses "Block Diffusion" for parallel drafting.
- Key Benefits: High speed (400+ tokens/sec), lossless quality, supports multiple popular models.
